0:46:29,52 --> 0:46:31,789
quicker than a hound dog
can smell a pole cat.


741
0:46:31,789 --> 0:46:33,457
That's very nice
of you, Mr. Keever


742
0:46:33,457 --> 0:46:35,959
but I'm a-waiting,
a friend, you know.


743
0:46:35,959 --> 0:46:38,228
Oh!


744
0:46:38,228 --> 0:46:41,331
The smell of winter's stouter
than horse radish.


745
0:46:41,331 --> 0:46:43,734
Hope it don't
kick up a rain.


746
0:46:43,734 --> 0:47:16,9
Goodbye.
Bye.


747
0:47:16,9 --> 0:47:18,68
Where you going?


748
0:47:18,68 --> 0:47:19,937
That a way.


749
0:47:19,937 --> 0:47:21,171
Just a stroll?


750
0:47:21,171 --> 0:47:23,507
Oh, no. Going to town.


751
0:47:23,507 --> 0:47:32,382
Smell of winter's
stouter than horse radish.


752
0:47:32,382 --> 0:47:34,184
Thought you told me
you'd never been to town.


753
0:47:34,184 --> 0:47:36,119
Might, might not.


754
0:47:36,119 --> 0:47:38,355
Hope it don't
kick up a rain.


755
0:47:38,355 --> 0:47:41,692
I give up.
Come on, get in.


756
0:47:41,692 --> 0:47:44,261
No. I wouldn't. It might be putting you out.


757
0:47:44,261 --> 0:47:46,33
It's only a short hop
and a tussle to town.


758
0:47:46,33 --> 0:47:53,403
Get in.


759
0:47:53,403 --> 0:47:55,839
Say, if it's any of my business,
why are you going to town?


760
0:47:55,839 --> 0:47:58,909
Education. Do you have to keep
your foot on the brake all the time?


761
0:47:58,909 --> 0:48:0,611
When did you
get that idea?


762
0:48:0,611 --> 0:48:1,945
I see you keep
jiggling it back and...


763
0:48:1,945 --> 0:48:4,314
You know what I mean.
When?


764
0:48:4,314 --> 0:48:5,782
Talking to people.


765
0:48:5,782 --> 0:48:7,117
Who?


766
0:48:7,117 --> 0:48:8,919
Oh, about.


767
0:48:8,919 --> 0:48:11,889
It was what
I told you, wasn't it?


768
0:48:11,889 --> 0:48:13,49
Did you?


769
0:48:13,49 --> 0:48:14,858
Yes, you was
one of them.


770
0:48:14,858 --> 0:48:16,56
I was all of them.


771
0:48:16,56 --> 0:48:19,897
Now see here, I meant what
I said. I sincerely meant it.


772
0:48:19,897 --> 0:48:21,965
But you're up to
something phony.


773
0:48:21,965 --> 0:48:23,934
People don't just get
an idea and then go.


774
0:48:23,934 --> 0:48:27,204
Did you ever stand under a falling
tree or see a pole cat back up?


775
0:48:27,204 --> 0:48:28,972
That's not funny.


776
0:48:28,972 --> 0:48:30,707
What did your father
say about it, and Dave?


777
0:48:30,707 --> 0:48:33,143
They was mostly agreeing,
especially Dave.


778
0:48:33,143 --> 0:48:34,745
He said when those checks
start traipsing in...


779
0:48:34,745 --> 0:48:36,914
I said that.


780
0:48:36,914 --> 0:48:48,659
All right, I'll walk.


781
0:48:48,659 --> 0:48:50,46
Same thing eating you?


782
0:48:50,46 --> 0:48:51,862
Huh?


783
0:48:51,862 --> 0:48:53,997
Sure makes me
feel bad.


784
0:48:53,997 --> 0:48:55,866
That's what I wanna
talk to you about.


785
0:48:55,866 --> 0:48:57,935
Nice of you. Horse gets out of the barn


786
0:48:57,935 --> 0:48:59,937
and now you want to
lock the door.


787
0:48:59,937 --> 0:49:2,239
Well, he ain't
got her yet.


788
0:49:2,239 --> 0:49:4,441
Who ain't got what...
Wait a minute.


789
0:49:4,441 --> 0:49:6,443
Ain't you and I talking
about the same thing?


790
0:49:6,443 --> 0:49:8,445
You bet we're talking
about the same thing.


791
0:49:8,445 --> 0:49:9,913
I was feeling
when he saved my life


792
0:49:9,913 --> 0:49:12,49
but I just didn't know
what it was then.


793
0:49:12,49 --> 0:49:16,153
Fever I says. Or maybe the lead's
splashing something in my eyes.


794
0:49:16,153 --> 0:49:18,155
But I ought to have known. It
was him being nice to Buddie.


795
0:49:18,155 --> 0:49:19,623
It was him...
Wait a minute, son.


796
0:49:19,623 --> 0:49:21,291
You're making
a gourd trap,


797
0:49:21,291 --> 0:49:24,962
but it's too big to catch meadow
larks and too small to catch ideas.


798
0:49:24,962 --> 0:49:26,697
What are you
talking about?


799
0:49:26,697 --> 0:49:27,864
Let's get June
right here.


800
0:49:27,864 --> 0:49:30,67
We ones is going to settle
this matter for good.


801
0:49:30,67 --> 0:49:32,402
You want her here?
Fine.


802
0:49:32,402 --> 0:49:33,937
You tell her
she could go to town,


803
0:49:33,937 --> 0:49:35,439
now you tell me
you want her here.


804
0:49:35,439 --> 0:49:36,84
Ain't you
a little tetched?


805
0:49:36,84 --> 0:49:38,41
I tell her
she can go where?


806
0:49:38,41 --> 0:49:39,543
Into town
to get educated.


807
0:49:39,543 --> 0:49:41,478
Got to read books,
she said you said.


808
0:49:41,478 --> 0:49:44,181
Don't want no cull for a
wife, she said you said.


809
0:49:44,181 --> 0:49:45,682
She said...
She ain't gone.


810
0:49:45,682 --> 0:49:46,783
You didn't
let her go, did you?


811
0:49:46,783 --> 0:49:48,919
Of course, been gone
maybe two hours now.


812
0:49:48,919 --> 0:49:51,254
Took her down to the ridge
to meet the mailman.


813
0:49:51,254 --> 0:49:53,23
She said...
It was him that done it.


814
0:49:53,23 --> 0:49:54,558
Him that said
he was our friend.


815
0:49:54,558 --> 0:49:56,26
That's why
he gave us the money.


816
0:49:56,26 --> 0:49:58,328
That's why he gave us
the money. You understand?


817
0:49:58,328 --> 0:49:59,396
He took her away.


818
0:49:59,396 --> 0:50:1,498
He's been wanting to take
her, but he was a-feared.


819
0:50:1,498 --> 0:50:2,866
All right.


820
0:50:2,866 --> 0:50:4,768
He thinks now maybe the money
will keep us from telling him


821
0:50:4,768 --> 0:50:7,27
that we ones up here
don't take nobody's woman.


822
0:50:7,27 --> 0:50:9,206
Money ain't
a- stopping us from that.


823
0:50:9,206 --> 0:50:10,307
Money ain't
a- stopping us from...


824
0:50:10,307 --> 0:50:12,809
Where are you going?


825
0:50:12,809 --> 0:50:19,85
I'm going hunting.


826
0:50:19,85 --> 0:50:21,818
You're sure
that was Dave Tolliver?


827
0:50:21,818 --> 0:50:24,888
He was a-headed for the camp
and across our property, too.


828
0:50:24,888 --> 0:50:27,624
If he's down there,
he's on our property.


829
0:50:27,624 --> 0:50:29,593
Might just as well
go down and look into it.


830
0:50:29,593 --> 0:50:31,94
That's my job.


831
0:50:31,94 --> 0:50:33,73
I've been sort of shamed since
I only get him in the arm.


832
0:50:33,73 --> 0:50:35,132
You're right.


833
0:50:35,132 --> 0:50:41,171
Rub out
the mistake, Son.


834
0:50:41,171 --> 0:50:43,14
So help me,
he isn't here.


835
0:50:43,14 --> 0:50:45,609
On my word of honor, he isn't
here. Do you understand me?


836
0:50:45,609 --> 0:50:46,843
Yeah.


837
0:50:46,843 --> 0:50:49,513
He went downtown.
Down to Gaptown, I mean.


838
0:50:49,513 --> 0:50:51,381
She didn't go with him?
No, I told you!


839
0:50:51,381 --> 0:50:53,316
He was alone, and... You sure
they didn't meet some place?


840
0:50:53,316 --> 0:50:54,918
With these, I saw him.


841
0:50:54,918 --> 0:50:58,388
He got into his wagon,
on this side...


842
0:50:58,388 --> 0:50:59,556
You ain't
answering my question.


843
0:50:59,556 --> 0:51:1,491
I can't answer
that 'cause I don't know.


844
0:51:1,491 --> 0:51:2,959
I watched him
there on the road.


845
0:51:2,959 --> 0:52:25,775
There was nobody
with him then, because...


846
0:52:25,775 --> 0:52:27,11
Mr. Thurber,
I'm a-quitting.


847
0:52:27,11 --> 0:52:28,311
No, you're not.


848
0:52:28,311 --> 0:52:29,88
In times like this,
you gotta be a man.


849
0:52:29,88 --> 0:52:31,214
A man must
never been a coward.


850
0:52:31,214 --> 0:52:33,683
I got to get to Gaptown to tell
the people down there what's up.


851
0:52:33,683 --> 0:52:35,619
But it's over.
There's nothing to tell!


852
0:52:35,619 --> 0:52:37,454
There ain't, eh?
You don't know.


853
0:52:37,454 --> 0:52:40,524
Look at here, Dave Tolliver's
gone to Gaptown to get Mr. Hale.


854
0:52:40,524 --> 0:52:42,259
He bust Wade Falin
on the beak.


855
0:52:42,259 --> 0:52:45,61
And when a Tolliver busts a
Falin on the beak, that means war.


856
0:52:45,61 --> 0:52:46,663
And I gotta tell
a- people in Gaptown,


857
0:52:46,663 --> 0:52:49,933
so they can
scuttle for safety.


858
0:52:49,933 --> 0:52:58,508
Good heavens!


859
0:52:58,508 --> 0:53:0,577
Jenkins.


860
0:53:0,577 --> 0:53:2,412
Jenkins.


861
0:53:2,412 --> 0:53:4,548
Biggest fight.
Outside camp.


862
0:53:4,548 --> 0:53:9,419
Wade Falin came down...
Dave Tolliver...


863
0:53:9,419 --> 0:53:18,862
And shoved him
over the cliff...


864
0:53:18,862 --> 0:53:21,431
I knew that thing was
going to break out again.


865
0:53:21,431 --> 0:53:29,94
Just a matter of time
and that's all we needed.


866
0:53:29,94 --> 0:53:31,408
And I was standing
right there.


867
0:53:31,408 --> 0:53:32,742
I heard enough.


868
0:53:32,742 --> 0:53:45,155
And he...


869
0:53:45,155 --> 0:53:46,69
Dave Tolliver
licked Wade Falin.


870
0:53:46,69 --> 0:53:55,365
And now he's coming
to get Mr. Hale.


871
0:53:55,365 --> 0:54:4,7
Whoa!


872
0:54:4,7 --> 0:54:5,742
Is there anything else you need? No.


873
0:54:5,742 --> 0:54:7,277
Well, if you think of
anything, just call the camp


874
0:54:7,277 --> 0:54:9,546
and I'll have one of
the men bring it down.


875
0:54:9,546 --> 0:54:11,915
I'm sorry, but...
Well?


876
0:54:11,915 --> 0:54:14,317
The room, you know, where Miss
Tolliver was going to stay...


877
0:54:14,317 --> 0:54:15,885
Well, that room,
I'm afraid...


878
0:54:15,885 --> 0:54:16,987
Afraid of what?


879
0:54:16,987 --> 0:54:18,321
Well, it ain't
a fitting place.


880
0:54:18,321 --> 0:54:19,589
It kind of leaks,
you know.


881
0:54:19,589 --> 0:54:22,592
Hold it. There's trouble,
ain't there?


882
0:54:22,592 --> 0:54:23,827
Trouble?


883
0:54:23,827 --> 0:54:25,962
I can smell it.
What's wrong?


884
0:54:25,962 --> 0:54:27,397
I don't want
no fighting.


885
0:54:27,397 --> 0:54:28,531
Fighting?


886
0:54:28,531 --> 0:54:30,2
Dave.


887
0:54:30,2 --> 0:54:31,368
Say, what is this?


888
0:54:31,368 --> 0:54:32,502
He's coming to get me.


889
0:54:32,502 --> 0:54:34,304
Who told you?
You've seen him?


890
0:54:34,304 --> 0:54:40,31
All town knows it. And I don't
want no trouble around here.


891
0:54:40,31 --> 0:54:41,745
You gotta go.


892
0:54:41,745 --> 0:54:43,146
I've got to what?


893
0:54:43,146 --> 0:54:47,5
I know... I've seen him the
time he shot down Jim Falin.


894
0:54:47,5 --> 0:54:48,251
You gotta
get out of town.


895
0:54:48,251 --> 0:54:50,153
What have I done to him that
he should want to harm me?


896
0:54:50,153 --> 0:54:51,354
Did I ever
do anything to him?


897
0:54:51,354 --> 0:54:52,522
No, you didn't.


898
0:54:52,522 --> 0:54:56,159
But I wish
I hadn't come down.


899
0:54:56,159 --> 0:54:57,761
Will you go?
Please go.


900
0:54:57,761 --> 0:54:58,862
You lied, didn't you?


901
0:54:58,862 --> 0:55:0,93
Everything you said coming
down out of the mountains?


902
0:55:0,93 --> 0:55:2,632
I knew you were lying then,
and something inside of me


903
0:55:2,632 --> 0:55:5,1
told me I should have
sent you home.


904
0:55:5,1 --> 0:55:7,103
Well, let him come.


905
0:55:7,103 --> 0:55:9,839
I never saw such a ferocious
look in a man's eyes in my life.


906
0:55:9,839 --> 0:55:16,212
I tell you, it's gonna be
the biggest fight of the year.


907
0:55:16,212 --> 0:55:18,715
Dave... Dave come out
of the tent, like a shot.


908
0:55:18,715 --> 0:55:20,317
He lit right on
top of Wade.


909
0:55:20,317 --> 0:55:22,852
And rammed down on him with
a right and left! Right!


910
0:55:22,852 --> 0:55:24,521
Wade got away from Dave.


911
0:55:24,521 --> 0:55:26,356
Dave got him right on the edge
of the cliff, he had him down,


912
0:55:26,356 --> 0:55:27,457
he was beating his head down and he says,


913
0:55:27,457 --> 0:55:29,92
"I'll kill you, I'll kill you, I'll kill you!


914
0:55:29,92 --> 0:55:30,493
"You'll take my girl,
will you?"


915
0:55:30,493 --> 0:55:33,63
He reached him up
and he says...


916
0:55:33,63 --> 0:55:35,532
Nice day, ain't it?


917
0:55:35,532 --> 0:55:39,269
Give me a beer.


918
0:55:39,269 --> 0:55:41,838
I gotta see somebody.


919
0:55:41,838 --> 0:55:44,407
Yeah, Dave Tolliver.


920
0:55:44,407 --> 0:55:47,41
And how'd you like to
tell him we was here.


921
0:55:47,41 --> 0:56:5,362
In the backroom.


922
0:56:5,362 --> 0:56:8,231
There's Dave Tolliver
coming in now.


923
0:56:8,231 --> 0:56:9,566
And he ain't going out.


924
0:56:9,566 --> 0:56:10,834
You can get him
right from here.


925
0:56:10,834 --> 0:56:13,503
We don't have to sneak
our shots at the Tolliver.


926
0:56:13,503 --> 0:56:15,171
Stay here, Wade.


927
0:56:15,171 --> 0:56:18,241
Hell.


928
0:56:18,241 --> 0:56:27,317
You sing about Stack O'Lee
and keep right on singing.


929
0:56:27,317 --> 0:56:30,72
<i>When the rain</i>
<i>was falling fast</i>


930
0:56:30,72 --> 0:56:33,69
<i>One dark and stormy night</i>


931
0:56:33,69 --> 0:56:40,163
<i>Stack O'Lee and Billy Lyons</i>
<i>Had an awful fight</i>


932
0:56:40,163 --> 0:56:49,773
<i>Bad, bad,</i>
<i>bad old Stack O'Lee</i>


933
0:56:49,773 --> 0:56:52,41
You ain't going to do nothing,
Dave. It's all my fault.


934
0:56:52,41 --> 0:56:53,977
Talk will keep.


935
0:56:53,977 --> 0:56:55,445
Now, let's get
this thing straight.


936
0:56:55,445 --> 0:56:57,113
You're down here
looking for trouble.


937
0:56:57,113 --> 0:56:59,616
I haven't done anything, but I
can see you won't believe that.


938
0:56:59,616 --> 0:57:6,523
All right.


939
0:57:6,523 --> 0:57:22,338
This is worth walking for.


940
0:57:22,338 --> 0:57:25,175
How are you doing, Buck?
Drop them gun.


941
0:57:25,175 --> 0:57:27,43
We're going about
our own business.


942
0:57:27,43 --> 0:57:30,246
Of course, you are.
Put them down.


943
0:57:30,246 --> 0:57:32,48
Certainly.


944
0:57:32,48 --> 0:57:34,35
Anything to oblige.


945
0:57:34,35 --> 0:57:36,719
Funny you ain't trying
to stop the fight.


946
0:57:36,719 --> 0:57:39,656
Fist fight
won't do no harm.


947
0:57:39,656 --> 0:57:41,825
Gun toting don't go.


948
0:57:41,825 --> 0:57:44,794
No hard feeling.


949
0:57:44,794 --> 0:57:46,963
No.


950
0:57:46,963 --> 0:58:13,189
No.


951
0:58:13,189 --> 0:58:25,602
You're doing a good job, Mr.
Hale. Maybe we can help you.


952
0:58:25,602 --> 0:58:27,804
So that's the way
it is, huh?


953
0:58:27,804 --> 0:58:28,872
Any way
you wanna look at it.


954
0:58:28,872 --> 0:58:40,617
You shouldn't
mess in old troubles.


955
0:58:40,617 --> 0:58:43,887
<i>Dogs did howl</i>


956
0:58:43,887 --> 0:58:46,723
<i>Dogs did bark</i>


957
0:58:46,723 --> 0:58:49,792
<i>When Stack O'Lee</i>
<i>the murderer</i>


958
0:58:49,792 --> 0:58:53,229
<i>went creeping</i>
<i>through the dark</i>


959
0:58:53,229 --> 0:59:22,825
<i>Bad, bad,</i>
<i>bad old Stack O'Lee</i>


960
0:59:22,825 --> 0:59:24,527
Get out of here
and take her with you!


961
0:59:24,527 --> 0:59:27,931
I can run from no Falin.


962
0:59:27,931 --> 0:59:32,368
I guess, here in the mountains
a woman doesn't mean very much.


963
0:59:32,368 --> 0:59:39,342
You came here to get her, didn't you?


964
0:59:39,342 --> 0:59:42,845
<i>Bam, bam, bam, bam</i>


965
0:59:42,845 --> 0:59:45,982
<i>Went Stack's. 44</i>


966
0:59:45,982 --> 0:59:48,718
<i>Next time I saw Billy Lyons</i>


967
0:59:48,718 --> 0:59:52,55
<i>He's stretched out</i>
<i>on the floor</i>


968
0:59:52,55 --> 0:59:58,394
<i>Bad, bad,</i>
<i>bad old Stack O'Lee</i>


969
0:59:58,394 --> 1:0:0,73
<i>Stop your drinking whiskey</i>


970
1:0:0,73 --> 1:0:3,333
<i>With your...</i>


971
1:0:3,333 --> 1:0:11,908
<i>Look what happened</i>
<i>to poor old Stack O'Lee</i>


972
1:0:11,908 --> 1:0:13,743
Okay, I'm licked.


973
1:0:13,743 --> 1:0:15,11
So what?


974
1:0:15,11 --> 1:0:17,413
You got lots to learn,
Mr. Hale, lots.


975
1:0:17,413 --> 1:0:18,715
I scratched
a bargain with you


976
1:0:18,715 --> 1:0:20,617
on a piece of paper,
and I kept it.


977
1:0:20,617 --> 1:0:23,252
But now, you're sticking your
nose in my personal affairs,


978
1:0:23,252 --> 1:0:25,455
so from now on
bargains don't count.


979
1:0:25,455 --> 1:0:42,71
And you won't be
long finding that out.


980
1:0:42,71 --> 1:0:48,344
Jack! Jack!


981
1:0:48,344 --> 1:0:50,546
Dave Tolliver!
He's coming to get you!


982
1:0:50,546 --> 1:0:53,449
There's going to
be a big fight.


983
1:0:53,449 --> 1:1:14,637
Is there?


984
1:1:14,637 --> 1:1:16,839
What are you doing here?


985
1:1:16,839 --> 1:1:18,207
I'm here 'cause
I ain't going back.


986
1:1:18,207 --> 1:1:19,509
I thought I told Dave
to take you...


987
1:1:19,509 --> 1:1:21,477
The sheriff said,
"I'm taking you


988
1:1:21,477 --> 1:1:23,78
"to the outskirts of town,
Dave Tolliver.


989
1:1:23,78 --> 1:1:25,481
"I'm leaving the rest
to your own judgment."


990
1:1:25,481 --> 1:1:26,716
Now see here, I'm not going to allow you...


991
1:1:26,716 --> 1:1:27,917
I ain't listening.


992
1:1:27,917 --> 1:1:30,687
You told me to get an education,
I'm getting an education.


993
1:1:30,687 --> 1:1:33,723
I'm staying here. If I can't stay
here, I'll stay where I can stay.


994
1:1:33,723 --> 1:1:35,758
You can't stop me,
nobody's gonna stop me!


995
1:1:35,758 --> 1:1:38,594
I'll show the whole kit and boodle
of you how much I can get learned.


996
1:1:38,594 --> 1:1:40,363
I'll be smarter than you!
That's what I'll be!


997
1:1:40,363 --> 1:1:42,265
Now listen, you little stick of dynamite.


998
1:1:42,265 --> 1:1:43,633
You're getting
out of here now.


999
1:1:43,633 --> 1:1:45,68
You're going back
up in the mountains.


1000
1:1:45,68 --> 1:1:46,703
I've heard enough of you
and I've seen enough of you.


1001
1:1:46,703 --> 1:1:50,873
For the present, at least.
Now, come on, get out.


1002
1:1:50,873 --> 1:1:54,43
You...


1003
1:1:54,43 --> 1:1:57,48
All right, I'll go


1004
1:1:57,48 --> 1:1:59,582
if you want me to go.


1005
1:1:59,582 --> 1:2:1,718
Sure.


1006
1:2:1,718 --> 1:2:5,688
I don't want people
not to want me.


1007
1:2:5,688 --> 1:2:7,724
Wait a minute.


1008
1:2:7,724 --> 1:2:9,726
How did you do that?


1009
1:2:9,726 --> 1:2:14,43
Oh, that.


1010
1:2:14,43 --> 1:2:18,468
You did it
when you pushed me down.


1011
1:2:18,468 --> 1:2:20,77
I'm sorry.


1012
1:2:20,77 --> 1:2:22,38
It might have been
a rusty nail or something.


1013
1:2:22,38 --> 1:2:30,646
We'd better fix it up.
Come over here.


1014
1:2:30,646 --> 1:2:32,949
So that's it, is it?


1015
1:2:32,949 --> 1:2:35,585
And I thought you were just
interested in the coal business.


1016
1:2:35,585 --> 1:2:36,753
She's hurt her hand.


1017
1:2:36,753 --> 1:2:40,123
You've killed your future,
around here, anyway.


1018
1:2:40,123 --> 1:2:42,558
You're not satisfied with
one enemy, you make two.


1019
1:2:42,558 --> 1:2:44,6
You realize
what you've done?


1020
1:2:44,6 --> 1:2:47,13
Now the Falins hate you, the
Tollivers will never forgive you.


1021
1:2:47,13 --> 1:2:49,31
The Tollivers, why?
That's why.


1022
1:2:49,31 --> 1:2:52,168
That girl's gonna go back
to the mountains, now.


1023
1:2:52,168 --> 1:2:54,737
She didn't come here to start
any trouble, it just happened.


1024
1:2:54,737 --> 1:2:57,573
She's got a mind of her own, and
if she wants to stay here she can.


1025
1:2:57,573 --> 1:2:58,975
In this town?
Lmpossible.


1026
1:2:58,975 --> 1:3:0,343
I'll take her
to Brighton.


1027
1:3:0,343 --> 1:3:2,245
Or Plenny or Sand Creek. It
doesn't matter where you take her


1028
1:3:2,245 --> 1:3:3,679
around here, you're about to meet Tollivers.


1029
1:3:3,679 --> 1:3:5,548
All right, I'll take her
to Louisville to my sister.


1030
1:3:5,548 --> 1:3:7,283
What do you think of that?
Nothing.


1031
1:3:7,283 --> 1:3:8,951
Except that
I'm flabbergasted.


1032
1:3:8,951 --> 1:3:10,386
Nonplussed.


1033
1:3:10,386 --> 1:3:11,654
And if you
don't mind me saying so,


1034
1:3:11,654 --> 1:3:15,825
I think you're just
a little bit nuts.


1035
1:3:15,825 --> 1:3:18,928
Thank you.


1036
1:3:18,928 --> 1:3:54,997
Both of you.


1037
1:3:54,997 --> 1:3:58,234
Mr. Hale! Oh, Mr. Hale!
You forgot the hat.


1038
1:3:58,234 --> 1:4:9,345
Thanks, Leo.


1039
1:4:9,345 --> 1:4:10,58
Well, here you are.


1040
1:4:10,58 --> 1:4:11,781
Do I...


1041
1:4:11,781 --> 1:4:14,183
Are you sure your sister will recognize me?


1042
1:4:14,183 --> 1:4:15,985
I don't see
how she can miss.


1043
1:4:15,985 --> 1:4:17,52
Do I look all right?


1044
1:4:17,52 --> 1:4:20,122
My dear young lady,
reticent as I am by nature,


1045
1:4:20,122 --> 1:4:21,691
it behooves me at this moment to tell you


1046
1:4:21,691 --> 1:4:23,626
that you're wearing the
finest the city affords.


1047
1:4:23,626 --> 1:4:25,862
All aboard!


1048
1:4:25,862 --> 1:4:32,368
Well, you better get on.


1049
1:4:32,368 --> 1:5:5,368
Ain't... Ain't you
gonna kiss me goodbye?


1050
1:5:5,368 --> 1:5:7,136
Well, that's over with.
Is it?


1051
1:5:7,136 --> 1:5:9,505
Yeah. What do
you mean, "Is it"?


1052
1:5:9,505 --> 1:5:11,7
No, I mean, I'm glad it's over with.


1053
1:5:11,7 --> 1:5:12,475
Are you?


1054
1:5:12,475 --> 1:5:14,143
She's nuts.
Is she?


1055
1:5:14,143 --> 1:5:15,778
Sure she is.
Any fool can see that.


1056
1:5:15,778 --> 1:5:17,88
Well, perhaps, that's
why I'm a little stupid.


1057
1:5:17,88 --> 1:5:19,248
Yeah, maybe that's...


1058
1:5:19,248 --> 1:5:20,917
Say, what is this
"isn't" and "is she"?


1059
1:5:20,917 --> 1:5:22,218
My dear fellow,
if you'll allow me,


1060
1:5:22,218 --> 1:5:24,654
let us take "isn't"
and "is she."


1061
1:5:24,654 --> 1:5:27,556
"Is" is that we both know,
I hope, is a verb.


1062
1:5:27,556 --> 1:5:30,326
"It" is a neuter gender,
and she is the feminine.


1063
1:5:30,326 --> 1:5:33,763
Thus, we have the neuter and
the feminine, but no masculine.


1064
1:5:33,763 --> 1:5:36,632
"What? No masculine,"
you say, then I say...


1065
1:5:36,632 --> 1:5:38,34
"I'm nuts,"
that's what you say.


1066
1:5:38,34 --> 1:5:39,702
Yeah, that's right,
you're nuts!


1067
1:5:39,702 --> 1:5:41,537
She's in love
with you, Jack.


1068
1:5:41,537 --> 1:5:43,506
In love? Who?
June.


1069
1:5:43,506 --> 1:5:44,74
Are you crazy?


1070
1:5:44,74 --> 1:5:45,841
No, no, that's already
been settled.


1071
1:5:45,841 --> 1:5:47,76
You're the one
who's crazy.


1072
1:5:47,76 --> 1:5:50,279
Why, she's been goo-gooing,
gee-geeing all over you


1073
1:5:50,279 --> 1:5:51,714
ever since
we started the camp.


1074
1:5:51,714 --> 1:5:53,549
Don't talk nonsense.


1075
1:5:53,549 --> 1:5:56,485
In love. Why, she only came
down to camp to bring Buddie.


1076
1:5:56,485 --> 1:5:58,12
In love with me.
You're an idiot.


1077
1:5:58,12 --> 1:5:59,855
I hope so.


1078
1:5:59,855 --> 1:6:8,931
I sincerely hope so.


1079
1:6:8,931 --> 1:7:9,558
The camp, Thurber.
It's on fire!


1080
1:7:9,558 --> 1:7:11,46
A bunch of fellows came over
the hill carrying torches.


1081
1:7:11,46 --> 1:7:12,795
The fellow leading
him was a-shooting.


1082
1:7:12,795 --> 1:7:14,63
The Falins.


1083
1:7:14,63 --> 1:7:16,32
Well... Never mind, we'll
talk about that later.


1084
1:7:16,32 --> 1:7:17,466
I'll get the stock
out of the corral.


1085
1:7:17,466 --> 1:8:20,996
You get the instruments
and maps out of there.


1086
1:8:20,996 --> 1:8:24,3
So that's how
you want it, is it?


1087
1:8:24,3 --> 1:8:27,603
All right, you skulking
coyotes, I'll play your game.


1088
1:8:27,603 --> 1:8:30,639
They're not gonna let me...


1089
1:8:30,639 --> 1:8:35,511
I'll put this road through if I have to
use your dirty rotten bodies for ties.


1090
1:8:35,511 --> 1:9:6,108
I'll do it if I have to hire every
man in Gaptown to finish the job.


1091
1:9:6,108 --> 1:9:7,409
If you
could have seen it


1092
1:9:7,409 --> 1:9:9,478
I know you would have split your sides a
- laughing.


1093
1:9:9,478 --> 1:9:13,315
I was sitting there mending, and I
hear the dripping and the sizzling,


1094
1:9:13,315 --> 1:9:15,885
and I says to myself,
I says, "I bet a rooster


1095
1:9:15,885 --> 1:9:17,887
"it's the soft soap
a- boiling over."


1096
1:9:17,887 --> 1:9:18,988
And sure enough...


1097
1:9:18,988 --> 1:9:21,757
Better try some of these
dandelion greens, son.


1098
1:9:21,757 --> 1:9:24,66
Zeke Denker fetched
them over this morning.


1099
1:9:24,66 --> 1:9:25,761
I ain't hungry.


1100
1:9:25,761 --> 1:9:27,363
But, David, you gotta eat something


1101
1:9:27,363 --> 1:9:29,698
after all the plowing
you've done.


1102
1:9:29,698 --> 1:9:31,634
Pappy.


1103
1:9:31,634 --> 1:9:35,37
A is the first letter
in the alphabet.


1104
1:9:35,37 --> 1:9:43,746
Because it means
"And" "Apple" and "Ax."


1105
1:9:43,746 --> 1:9:45,681
What's this one, Pappy?


1106
1:9:45,681 --> 1:9:49,752
You mean this one?


1107
1:9:49,752 --> 1:9:52,922
Offhand I'd say
it's alike an ox yoke.


1108
1:9:52,922 --> 1:9:55,391
Didn't Mr. Hale tell you?


1109
1:9:55,391 --> 1:9:57,293
He told me
but I forgot.


1110
1:9:57,293 --> 1:10:0,95
It ain't like
no Tolliver to forget.


1111
1:10:0,95 --> 1:10:4,33
Now, if I would
have been told...


1112
1:10:4,33 --> 1:10:7,703
You know what that is?


1113
1:10:7,703 --> 1:10:9,371
Yeah.


1114
1:10:9,371 --> 1:10:16,178
Civilization!


1115
1:10:16,178 --> 1:10:17,546
David, you oughtn't
to have done that!


1116
1:10:17,546 --> 1:10:18,881
I'm through pretending.


1117
1:10:18,881 --> 1:10:20,649
Like you've been doing
all of last month.


1118
1:10:20,649 --> 1:10:21,85
Saying things
you didn't mean.


1119
1:10:21,85 --> 1:10:23,18
I'm getting sick
of the whole thing.


1120
1:10:23,18 --> 1:10:26,121
Now, son, look, you gotta keep your shirt on.


1121
1:10:26,121 --> 1:10:29,825
If it's June you're worrying
about, she'll be back pretty short.


1122
1:10:29,825 --> 1:10:30,96
No, she ain't.


1123
1:10:30,96 --> 1:10:33,262
She ain't never coming back.
Not the June I know.


1124
1:10:33,262 --> 1:10:35,231
Ain't nothing gonna
be the way it was.


1125
1:10:35,231 --> 1:10:38,133
Look at Buddie,
even he's different.


1126
1:10:38,133 --> 1:10:39,935
So are you.
Me?


1127
1:10:39,935 --> 1:10:41,27
Yes, you are.


1128
1:10:41,27 --> 1:10:43,872
Them new fangled machines
down in Ticopi that's doing it.


1129
1:10:43,872 --> 1:10:45,341
Every day you traipse down there with Buddie


1130
1:10:45,341 --> 1:10:46,775
and you come back
being different.


1131
1:10:46,775 --> 1:10:48,477
Half the time
you're feeling glad.


1132
1:10:48,477 --> 1:10:50,879
Like last week, they
tore up one of our fields.


1133
1:10:50,879 --> 1:10:53,582
Them machines don't care who's
been plowing there for 50 years.


1134
1:10:53,582 --> 1:10:55,618
The Tollivers don't mean nothing to them.


1135
1:10:55,618 --> 1:10:57,453
I ain't nobody
with a high temper.


1136
1:10:57,453 --> 1:10:59,255
But you're talking
unreasonable.


1137
1:10:59,255 --> 1:11:0,756
We're getting rich,
ain't we?


1138
1:11:0,756 --> 1:11:3,125
Look at them five checks
over there in that bowl.


1139
1:11:3,125 --> 1:11:4,36
Half of them is yours.


1140
1:11:4,36 --> 1:11:7,296
And how did we get them?
Just doing nothing.


1141
1:11:7,296 --> 1:11:10,499
And if that's what you call
civilization, then I'm for it.


1142
1:11:10,499 --> 1:11:12,868
Judd!
He needs a-talking to.


1143
1:11:12,868 --> 1:11:15,4
It ain't right for no young
man to brood about nothing.


1144
1:11:15,4 --> 1:11:16,939
This you call
nothing, huh?


1145
1:11:16,939 --> 1:11:18,54
Listen, there's got to
be a change, you see?


1146
1:11:18,54 --> 1:11:19,875
Not for me,
there ain't.


1147
1:11:19,875 --> 1:11:21,76
There ain't no more
chance of me changing


1148
1:11:21,76 --> 1:11:23,412
than there is of that old Lonesome
Pine changed into a hickory.


1149
1:11:23,412 --> 1:11:25,581
I belong to the earth.
The plowed up soil.


1150
1:11:25,581 --> 1:11:27,516
I was raised and
I'm gonna die in it.


1151
1:11:27,516 --> 1:11:29,51
You got what you like?
You can have it.


1152
1:11:29,51 --> 1:11:34,69
Me, I'm going back. Back
where my pappy raised me.


1153
1:11:34,69 --> 1:11:36,625
David, you can't
do that.


1154
1:11:36,625 --> 1:11:39,595
You're our boy.
I mean, you're like our boy.


1155
1:11:39,595 --> 1:11:45,868
I ain't a-wanting
you to go.


1156
1:11:45,868 --> 1:11:49,238
Two pink-eyed doves
sitting in a tree,


1157
1:11:49,238 --> 1:11:51,74
one for you, one for me.


1158
1:11:51,74 --> 1:12:19,735
For June.


1159
1:12:19,735 --> 1:12:26,275
<i>For when</i>
<i>it's twilight on the trail</i>


1160
1:12:26,275 --> 1:12:30,346
<i>And I jog along</i>


1161
1:12:30,346 --> 1:12:34,95
<i>The world is like a dream</i>


1162
1:12:34,95 --> 1:12:39,655
<i>And the ripple</i>
<i>of the stream</i>


1163
1:12:39,655 --> 1:12:43,559
<i>Is my song</i>


1164
1:12:43,559 --> 1:13:5,981
<i>For when it's twilight</i>
<i>on the trail</i>


1165
1:13:5,981 --> 1:13:8,417
Hello?


1166
1:13:8,417 --> 1:13:12,221
Well, well, well,
Miss Tolliver.


1167
1:13:12,221 --> 1:13:13,389
What, again?


1168
1:13:13,389 --> 1:13:14,49
Obviously.


1169
1:13:14,49 --> 1:13:16,658
Do I tell her
you're out to tea?


1170
1:13:16,658 --> 1:13:21,964
No, I'll talk to her.


1171
1:13:21,964 --> 1:13:24,767
You'd better go out and check
with Marks about those uprights.


1172
1:13:24,767 --> 1:13:27,469
Naturally.


1173
1:13:27,469 --> 1:13:28,771
Hello, June.


1174
1:13:28,771 --> 1:13:31,273
Are you mad at somebody
or something?


1175
1:13:31,273 --> 1:13:34,61
Well, you talk like it.


1176
1:13:34,61 --> 1:13:37,112
Oh, yeah.


1177
1:13:37,112 --> 1:13:39,415
Busy? You don't know
what busy means.


1178
1:13:39,415 --> 1:13:40,749
I ain't...


1179
1:13:40,749 --> 1:13:44,52
I mean, I haven't
had a minute to myself.


1180
1:13:44,52 --> 1:13:46,755
This morning I learnt
all about the Revolution.


1181
1:13:46,755 --> 1:13:49,358
It was just like a feud.


1182
1:13:49,358 --> 1:13:52,294
In 1775...


1183
1:13:52,294 --> 1:13:54,563
Wait a minute, June.
Come in.


1184
1:13:54,563 --> 1:13:56,432
Mr. Hale, we've got that slue banked.


1185
1:13:56,432 --> 1:13:57,766
That's fine, Taylor.


1186
1:13:57,766 --> 1:14:0,2
Wait a minute, get the steam
shovel out on the bridge


1187
1:14:0,2 --> 1:14:1,603
so we can start to
fill in the morning.


1188
1:14:1,603 --> 1:14:3,105
Yes, sir.


1189
1:14:3,105 --> 1:14:5,541
Yeah, June?


1190
1:14:5,541 --> 1:14:7,142
Yeah.


1191
1:14:7,142 --> 1:14:10,779
But that wasn't Patrick Henry,
that was Lord Cornwallis.


1192
1:14:10,779 --> 1:14:12,8
Cornwallis.


1193
1:14:12,8 --> 1:14:13,649
All right. Cornwallis.


1194
1:14:13,649 --> 1:14:17,453
What difference
does it make?


1195
1:14:17,453 --> 1:14:20,589
How are you?


1196
1:14:20,589 --> 1:14:23,926
How's Pappy and Mammy
and Buddie?


1197
1:14:23,926 --> 1:14:25,6
They are?


1198
1:14:25,6 --> 1:14:33,702
Yeah.


1199
1:14:33,702 --> 1:14:37,739
Say, June, you know you've
got the prettiest eyes.


1200
1:14:37,739 --> 1:14:40,108
Yeah.


1201
1:14:40,108 --> 1:14:44,847
And the cutest nose.


1202
1:14:44,847 --> 1:14:56,558
Say, have you
got a dimple?


1203
1:14:56,558 --> 1:14:58,26
You get a fix, Son?


1204
1:14:58,26 --> 1:15:0,162
She's all sort onto the
bridge and ready to go.


1205
1:15:0,162 --> 1:15:1,864
We'll pop her off
in the morning.


1206
1:15:1,864 --> 1:15:28,59
Kind of like to have
Mr. Hale see it.


1207
1:15:28,59 --> 1:15:30,158
Hey, Pappy.


1208
1:15:30,158 --> 1:15:34,696
Now we're here
for Mr. Corsey?


1209
1:15:34,696 --> 1:15:36,698
Yeah, but you stay right here till your pappy


1210
1:15:36,698 --> 1:15:38,634
gets through talking
to Mr. Hale.


1211
1:15:38,634 --> 1:15:57,719
Thanks, Pappy.


1212
1:15:57,719 --> 1:16:0,88
Can I come in,
Mr. Hale?


1213
1:16:0,88 --> 1:16:4,326
Sure, come on in.


1214
1:16:4,326 --> 1:16:7,329
I got serious things to
talk to you about, Mr. Hale.


1215
1:16:7,329 --> 1:16:17,539
Sit down.


1216
1:16:17,539 --> 1:16:19,441
And now, it's Dave
that's going away.


1217
1:16:19,441 --> 1:16:20,943
It's gotten me worried.


1218
1:16:20,943 --> 1:16:22,678
About Melissa, I mean.


1219
1:16:22,678 --> 1:16:24,88
She don't sing
no more, Mr. Hale.


1220
1:16:24,88 --> 1:16:27,716
Sun up always seen her singing, you know?


1221
1:16:27,716 --> 1:16:30,285
I'm sorry about Melissa,
but there's nothing I can do.


1222
1:16:30,285 --> 1:16:31,853
I got troubles of my own.


1223
1:16:31,853 --> 1:16:33,822
You gotta come, Mr. Hale.


1224
1:16:33,822 --> 1:16:36,325
Melissa,
she'll listen to you.


1225
1:16:36,325 --> 1:16:38,594
Somehow, I don't talk
the right language to her.


1226
1:16:38,594 --> 1:16:40,996
No wonder you can't speak a
language which Melissa understands.


1227
1:16:40,996 --> 1:16:43,165
I've never heard her favor
your feud to the Falins.


1228
1:16:43,165 --> 1:16:45,4
Have you done anything to
stop it? No, you haven't.


1229
1:16:45,4 --> 1:16:46,635
You came down here
to blame me


1230
1:16:46,635 --> 1:16:48,403
for June's going away
and for Dave's leaving.


1231
1:16:48,403 --> 1:16:50,205
You'd like to
thrust the responsibility


1232
1:16:50,205 --> 1:16:51,94
for Melissa's suffering
on my shoulders.


1233
1:16:51,94 --> 1:17:5,454
Well, you don't do it. I've got enough
of you and your whole stupid outfit.


1234
1:17:5,454 --> 1:17:7,22
I'm sorry, Judd, I...


1235
1:17:7,22 --> 1:17:9,791
I didn't really mean
what I said.


1236
1:17:9,791 --> 1:17:11,66
Sure glad.


1237
1:17:11,66 --> 1:17:16,898
I liked you the first day
you walked into my house.


1238
1:17:16,898 --> 1:17:20,302
Wait a minute.


1239
1:17:20,302 --> 1:17:22,237
Hello?


1240
1:17:22,237 --> 1:17:24,439
Yes, Hale speaking.


1241
1:17:24,439 --> 1:17:27,275
Louisville?
Just a minute.


1242
1:17:27,275 --> 1:17:30,212
You wanna
speak to June?


1243
1:17:30,212 --> 1:17:31,313
Can I?


1244
1:17:31,313 --> 1:17:33,181
Come here.


1245
1:17:33,181 --> 1:17:39,521
<i>Hold that up to your ear.</i>


1246
1:17:39,521 --> 1:17:41,757
Now, talk right in here.


1247
1:17:41,757 --> 1:17:43,125
What for?


1248
1:17:43,125 --> 1:17:45,193
Well, you wanna speak
to June, don't you?


1249
1:17:45,193 --> 1:17:46,862
But you said
she was in Louisville.


1250
1:17:46,862 --> 1:17:52,801
Well, that's where
she is.


1251
1:17:52,801 --> 1:17:55,404
<i>Hello, Pappy.</i>


1252
1:17:55,404 --> 1:17:58,306
June.


1253
1:17:58,306 --> 1:17:59,841
Where are you hiding?


1254
1:17:59,841 --> 1:18:4,946
I'm not hiding, Pappy.
I'm in Louisville.


1255
1:18:4,946 --> 1:18:6,415
She says
she's in Louisville.


1256
1:18:6,415 --> 1:18:9,518
Well, that's what
I told you.


1257
1:18:9,518 --> 1:18:11,119
Is this thing hollow
all the way through?


1258
1:18:11,119 --> 1:18:12,621
Yeah, all the way through.


1259
1:18:12,621 --> 1:18:19,461
Well...


1260
1:18:19,461 --> 1:18:48,356
Hello, little brush rabbit.


1261
1:18:48,356 --> 1:18:53,261
You didn't, huh?


1262
1:18:53,261 --> 1:19:17,552
You know what your ma said
this morning?


1263
1:19:17,552 --> 1:19:23,358
Operator?


1264
1:19:23,358 --> 1:19:30,398
Buddie!
Buddie is in there.


1265
1:19:30,398 --> 1:19:32,601
Buddie.


1266
1:19:32,601 --> 1:19:34,369
Pappy.


1267
1:19:34,369 --> 1:19:36,37
Jack.


1268
1:19:36,37 --> 1:19:42,844
Pappy!


1269
1:19:42,844 --> 1:19:47,349
Buddie! Buddie!


1270
1:19:47,349 --> 1:19:55,457
Buddie!


1271
1:19:55,457 --> 1:19:59,928
<i></i>


1272
1:19:59,928 --> 1:20:2,43
Buddie. Buddie.


1273
1:20:2,43 --> 1:20:5,567
<i>Get me Dr. Owen, quick.</i>


1274
1:20:5,567 --> 1:20:12,908
Get me some hot water.


1275
1:20:12,908 --> 1:20:16,978
Buddie.


1276
1:20:16,978 --> 1:20:20,682
Son. It's your pappy, Son.


1277
1:20:20,682 --> 1:20:23,451
Oh, God,
don't let him die.


1278
1:20:23,451 --> 1:20:28,69
Don't take him away
from my poor Melissa.


1279
1:20:28,69 --> 1:20:32,527
Buddie.


1280
1:20:32,527 --> 1:21:20,609
<i>Buddie.</i>


1281
1:21:20,609 --> 1:21:22,811
You may be the civil law
around here, but get this,


1282
1:21:22,811 --> 1:21:25,146
interference with the public
carriers, the railroad, I mean,


1283
1:21:25,146 --> 1:21:26,681
that's a federal offense.


1284
1:21:26,681 --> 1:21:28,183
It might have been
an accident.


1285
1:21:28,183 --> 1:21:30,185
But it wasn't!


1286
1:21:30,185 --> 1:21:31,553
It was cold wanton murder!


1287
1:21:31,553 --> 1:21:34,522
They killed little Buddie!
They murdered him! A baby!


1288
1:21:34,522 --> 1:21:36,358
And I'm gonna put them
where they rot.


1289
1:21:36,358 --> 1:21:38,627
Not for a murder, your
heels are too smart for that.


1290
1:21:38,627 --> 1:21:41,263
And there's not a man in this town
with courage enough to convict him.


1291
1:21:41,263 --> 1:21:43,531
But you're gonna make out
a warrant on my charges!


1292
1:21:43,531 --> 1:21:44,933
You're gonna do what I say.


1293
1:21:44,933 --> 1:21:46,935
And you're gonna do
everything I say.


1294
1:21:46,935 --> 1:21:51,206
Mr. Hale, I've lived in this
country for more than 50 years.


1295
1:21:51,206 --> 1:21:54,409
I was born here,
and I know these people.


1296
1:21:54,409 --> 1:21:57,812
I can bring the Falins
to court. Maybe hang them.


1297
1:21:57,812 --> 1:22:1,16
But that don't stop feuds.
It makes them.


1298
1:22:1,16 --> 1:22:4,219
There'd be killings like
we've never seen before.


1299
1:22:4,219 --> 1:22:7,122
Mountain people don't
seem to like law, Mr. Hale.


1300
1:22:7,122 --> 1:22:10,959
Down here, peace has got to come from within.


1301
1:22:10,959 --> 1:22:13,461
It all seems kind of brutal and
primitive while it's a-boiling,


1302
1:22:13,461 --> 1:22:17,599
but, well, I was born here and I know.


1303
1:22:17,599 --> 1:22:20,435
I'm talking honest,
Mr. Hale.


1304
1:22:20,435 --> 1:22:22,137
You know, I...


1305
1:22:22,137 --> 1:22:25,307
I cried when they told me
Buddie was killed.


1306
1:22:25,307 --> 1:22:27,8
Why, I used to ride miles
out of my way


1307
1:22:27,8 --> 1:22:29,21
to fetch him
some stick candy.


1308
1:22:29,21 --> 1:22:31,813
But I like Jim Falin, too.


1309
1:22:31,813 --> 1:22:34,82
That was before
you come here.


1310
1:22:34,82 --> 1:22:37,452
He's older than Buddie
but just a kid.


1311
1:22:37,452 --> 1:22:39,621
Eyes always a-laughing.


1312
1:22:39,621 --> 1:22:42,624
He was
Buck's favorite son.


1313
1:22:42,624 --> 1:22:44,859
Dave Tolliver shot him.


1314
1:22:44,859 --> 1:22:47,28
Had reasons, I guess.


1315
1:22:47,28 --> 1:22:48,697
Or I could have
cramped him in jail.


1316
1:22:48,697 --> 1:22:50,498
Yes, I could.


1317
1:22:50,498 --> 1:22:54,636
But did you ever get up close to
Melissa and look into her eyes?


1318
1:22:54,636 --> 1:22:55,837
Well, you do that
sometime.


1319
1:22:55,837 --> 1:22:57,806
Then you tell me
what kind of a law


1320
1:22:57,806 --> 1:23:1,9
you can think of
that will correct it.


1321
1:23:1,9 --> 1:23:11,987
Tell me...
June!


1322
1:23:11,987 --> 1:23:15,623
He couldn't just die,
could he?


1323
1:23:15,623 --> 1:23:18,126
He had to be killed.


1324
1:23:18,126 --> 1:23:20,28
Killed by the Falin.


1325
1:23:20,28 --> 1:23:22,263
They did that.


1326
1:23:22,263 --> 1:23:24,165
He was my only brother.


1327
1:23:24,165 --> 1:23:26,968
And they killed him.


1328
1:23:26,968 --> 1:23:30,538
He ran down the hill with
me before I went away.


1329
1:23:30,538 --> 1:23:33,942
He stood up there
at the Lonesome Pine.


1330
1:23:33,942 --> 1:23:37,479
I never got to
see him again.


1331
1:23:37,479 --> 1:23:41,75
I'm never going to
see him again.


1332
1:23:41,75 --> 1:23:43,351
What are you doing here?


1333
1:23:43,351 --> 1:23:46,521
Why aren't you up there
with Dave and Daddy?


1334
1:23:46,521 --> 1:23:48,423
You loved Buddie,
didn't you?


1335
1:23:48,423 --> 1:23:51,659
You said you loved him.


1336
1:23:51,659 --> 1:23:53,528
He was gonna be an engineer.


1337
1:23:53,528 --> 1:23:57,432
Like you and Corsey.


1338
1:23:57,432 --> 1:24:1,569
When I tucked him in
at night, he said,


1339
1:24:1,569 --> 1:24:7,842
"A is for apple, and I'll bet
you I'll be as big as Mr. Hale."


1340
1:24:7,842 --> 1:24:9,144
What are you doing here?


1341
1:24:9,144 --> 1:24:11,112
June.


1342
1:24:11,112 --> 1:24:13,14
You're down here
with the law!


1343
1:24:13,14 --> 1:24:14,949
The law's gonna help you!


1344
1:24:14,949 --> 1:24:17,519
The laws gonna show you
how it don't hurt.


1345
1:24:17,519 --> 1:24:19,587
When somebody you love...


1346
1:24:19,587 --> 1:24:20,722
When somebody you love...


1347
1:24:20,722 --> 1:24:21,79
Oh, June, darling,
don't cry.


1348
1:24:21,79 --> 1:24:24,559
You mustn't cry.
Listen to me, dear.


1349
1:24:24,559 --> 1:24:28,763
I love you, and...


1350
1:24:28,763 --> 1:24:31,132
You love me?


1351
1:24:31,132 --> 1:24:33,868
You said
you loved Buddie.


1352
1:24:33,868 --> 1:24:35,937
Why aren't you
with Buddie?


1353
1:24:35,937 --> 1:24:38,339
Why aren't you
where they need you?


1354
1:24:38,339 --> 1:24:40,308
You're here
with the law.


1355
1:24:40,308 --> 1:24:41,509
You don't love me!


1356
1:24:41,509 --> 1:24:43,578
Well, I do
with all of my heart.


1357
1:24:43,578 --> 1:24:48,516
You never said you love me before
and I was hungry to hear it.


1358
1:24:48,516 --> 1:24:50,452
You said
you love Buddie.


1359
1:24:50,452 --> 1:24:52,72
But you ain't
doing nothing about it!


1360
1:24:52,72 --> 1:24:55,423
You ain't fighting!
You ain't killing!


1361
1:24:55,423 --> 1:25:1,396
That's what's coming to them! The Falins!


1362
1:25:1,396 --> 1:25:3,398
This is what you wanted me to be, ain't it?


1363
1:25:3,398 --> 1:25:6,167
Pretty, nice words,
hollow words!


1364
1:25:6,167 --> 1:25:7,735
I don't want it!


1365
1:25:7,735 --> 1:25:10,138
I don't want you!
I don't want anything!


1366
1:25:10,138 --> 1:25:39,801
I don't want anything
but the Falins!


1367
1:25:39,801 --> 1:25:43,671
Our Father who art in
Heaven, hallowed be thy name.


1368
1:25:43,671 --> 1:25:46,975
Thy Kingdom come. Thy will be done on earth


1369
1:25:46,975 --> 1:25:48,743
as it is in Heaven.


1370
1:25:48,743 --> 1:25:52,48
Give us this day our daily bread
and forgive us our trespasses


1371
1:25:52,48 --> 1:25:56,251
as we forgive those who trespass against us.


1372
1:25:56,251 --> 1:26:1,256
Lead us not into temptation
but deliver us from evil.


1373
1:26:1,256 --> 1:26:6,261
For thine is the power and
the glory forever and ever.


1374
1:26:6,261 --> 1:26:18,473
Amen.


1375
1:26:18,473 --> 1:26:26,648
<i>When it's twilight</i>
<i>on the trail</i>


1376
1:26:26,648 --> 1:26:32,72
<i>And I rest once more</i>


1377
1:26:32,72 --> 1:26:37,458
<i>My ceiling is the sky</i>


1378
1:26:37,458 --> 1:26:40,495
<i>And the grass</i>


1379
1:26:40,495 --> 1:26:43,531
<i>On which I lie</i>


1380
1:26:43,531 --> 1:26:49,404
<i>Is my floor</i>


1381
1:26:49,404 --> 1:26:58,613
<i>When it's twilight</i>
<i>on the trail</i>


1382
1:26:58,613 --> 1:27:5,82
<i>And my voice is still</i>


1383
1:27:5,82 --> 1:27:9,39
<i>Please plant</i>
<i>this heart of mine</i>


1384
1:27:9,39 --> 1:27:16,598
<i>Underneath the Lonesome Pine</i>


1385
1:27:16,598 --> 1:27:28,76
<i>On the hill</i>


1386
1:27:28,76 --> 1:27:33,248
Oh, God, our Heavenly Father, we
bow before thee in meekest humbleness


1387
1:27:33,248 --> 1:27:38,786
leaving in thy divine wisdom and
accepting with equal humbleness


1388
1:27:38,786 --> 1:27:41,956
the complexities
of this life.


1389
1:27:41,956 --> 1:27:47,128
We are returning to the earth
that which thou has produced.


1390
1:27:47,128 --> 1:28:37,612
A part of thy soul,
of life eternal.


1391
1:28:37,612 --> 1:28:40,882
There's just about
eight of them, Judd.


1392
1:28:40,882 --> 1:28:42,383
Dominickers!


1393
1:28:42,383 --> 1:28:45,219
Looks like things is just
born to the Tollivers.


1394
1:28:45,219 --> 1:28:47,422
Don't it, Melissa?


1395
1:28:47,422 --> 1:28:50,258
Sure seems.


1396
1:28:50,258 --> 1:28:51,693
What are we
going to do?


1397
1:28:51,693 --> 1:28:53,194
What are we
standing here for?


1398
1:28:53,194 --> 1:28:54,662
June, honey.


1399
1:28:54,662 --> 1:28:56,998
I'm not just gonna
stand around any longer.


1400
1:28:56,998 --> 1:29:7,75
Be sensible.


1401
1:29:7,75 --> 1:29:8,943
Before green-up
time, Dave.


1402
1:29:8,943 --> 1:29:15,45
That's what you want,
isn't it?


1403
1:29:15,45 --> 1:29:16,684
You mean it?


1404
1:29:16,684 --> 1:29:20,88
It's gotta be somebody
who acts like a Tolliver.


1405
1:29:20,88 --> 1:29:33,968
Is that what
it's going to be?


1406
1:29:33,968 --> 1:29:35,903
Dave, I don't
want you to go.


1407
1:29:35,903 --> 1:29:38,706
I ain't hating the Falins.
I ain't hating nobody.


1408
1:29:38,706 --> 1:29:40,441
I ain't grieving
for Buddie.


1409
1:29:40,441 --> 1:29:42,477
June's my sorrow now.


1410
1:29:42,477 --> 1:29:44,912
I don't want to
go on hating.


1411
1:29:44,912 --> 1:29:48,182
Don't go, David.


1412
1:29:48,182 --> 1:29:50,952
Dave...
Wait a minute.


1413
1:29:50,952 --> 1:29:52,887
Dave, you're not going to
let him... Dave, listen.


1414
1:29:52,887 --> 1:29:56,157
You can't do this thing. You've
got green-up time to think about.


1415
1:29:56,157 --> 1:29:58,92
You'll be
getting married, then.


1416
1:29:58,92 --> 1:30:0,495
Now you're going out and
run the risk of being killed.


1417
1:30:0,495 --> 1:30:2,163
Hasn't there been enough
unhappiness in this house?


1418
1:30:2,163 --> 1:30:3,264
You ain't a Tolliver.


1419
1:30:3,264 --> 1:30:4,332
You're an outsider.


1420
1:30:4,332 --> 1:30:5,9
Yes. Well, none of you could have


1421
1:30:5,9 --> 1:30:7,902
loved little Buddie
any better than I did.


1422
1:30:7,902 --> 1:30:10,872
And he was killed because I taught
him to love the things I did.


1423
1:30:10,872 --> 1:30:12,507
It was my fault.


1424
1:30:12,507 --> 1:30:15,376
And this matter of getting
even is gonna be my business.


1425
1:30:15,376 --> 1:30:17,612
It's gonna be my business until
I've cleaned out every Falin


1426
1:30:17,612 --> 1:30:23,918
that had anything
to do with it.


1427
1:30:23,918 --> 1:30:39,367
Jack! Jack!


1428
1:30:39,367 --> 1:30:41,202
Dave.


1429
1:30:41,202 --> 1:30:42,77
I didn't want him to go.


1430
1:30:42,77 --> 1:30:45,173
I wouldn't have
let you go, either.


1431
1:30:45,173 --> 1:30:48,91
I would have
stopped you.


1432
1:30:48,91 --> 1:30:53,781
I only said those things
'cause I was hurt inside.


1433
1:30:53,781 --> 1:30:55,616
I could've stopped you.


1434
1:30:55,616 --> 1:30:57,418
But he's different.


1435
1:30:57,418 --> 1:31:0,655
He's not like a brother.


1436
1:31:0,655 --> 1:31:3,524
He'll never come back.


1437
1:31:3,524 --> 1:31:7,862
He'll never
wanna come back.


1438
1:31:7,862 --> 1:31:10,331
Dave.


1439
1:31:10,331 --> 1:31:11,933
Stop him.


1440
1:31:11,933 --> 1:31:15,837
Tell him what I can't.


1441
1:31:15,837 --> 1:31:39,126
Please, Dave.


1442
1:31:39,126 --> 1:31:40,495
You ain't going
to no Falins.


1443
1:31:40,495 --> 1:31:42,763
No? Well,
you try and stop me.


1444
1:31:42,763 --> 1:32:19,267
You're looking for trouble, Mr.
Hale, the mountains is full of it.


1445
1:32:19,267 --> 1:32:21,369
We're all brave men.


1446
1:32:21,369 --> 1:32:24,5
Falins are brave men.


1447
1:32:24,5 --> 1:32:25,206
You killed
the children.


1448
1:32:25,206 --> 1:32:27,8
I didn't know.


1449
1:32:27,8 --> 1:32:29,43
It's done now.


1450
1:32:29,43 --> 1:32:31,946
Sometime,
I'll wanna go downtown.


1451
1:32:31,946 --> 1:32:34,649
People, they'll look at me.


1452
1:32:34,649 --> 1:32:39,62
Maybe when I ain't around,
they'll call me Herod.


1453
1:32:39,62 --> 1:32:42,123
Herod Falin.


1454
1:32:42,123 --> 1:32:44,592
They might call me that.


1455
1:32:44,592 --> 1:32:46,761
He was a fellow
that done that once.


1456
1:32:46,761 --> 1:32:48,129
He killed babies.


1457
1:32:48,129 --> 1:32:49,997
The kid was a Tolliver,
wasn't he?


1458
1:32:49,997 --> 1:32:51,866
You're kind of forgetting
about Jim, ain't you?


1459
1:32:51,866 --> 1:32:53,601
I ain't
forgetting nothing.


1460
1:32:53,601 --> 1:32:56,704
Jim told me, in my arms, he
was hiding behind the bushes


1461
1:32:56,704 --> 1:32:58,573
trying to pick off
Dave Tolliver,


1462
1:32:58,573 --> 1:33:1,275
and Dave couldn't see
who he was shooting at.


1463
1:33:1,275 --> 1:33:4,912
Buddie Tolliver
couldn't say that.


1464
1:33:4,912 --> 1:33:7,248
I don't like him and
I ain't gonna like him.


1465
1:33:7,248 --> 1:33:13,854
I get my hands
on that Dave Tolliver...


1466
1:33:13,854 --> 1:33:15,156
Who's that?


1467
1:33:15,156 --> 1:33:24,398
Dave Tolliver.


1468
1:33:24,398 --> 1:33:26,33
What are you here for?


1469
1:33:26,33 --> 1:33:27,535
I wanna talk to you.


1470
1:33:27,535 --> 1:33:41,315
And I ain't carry no gun.


1471
1:33:41,315 --> 1:33:51,726
